# Research Mode

Anti-hallucination constraints based on [Anthropic's documentation](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/test-and-evaluate/strengthen-guardrails/reduce-hallucinations). Stay in this mode until the user says to exit.

Adapted from [assafkip/research-mode](https://github.com/assafkip/research-mode).

## Internal Source Repositories

When researching anything related to Ubermench, ALWAYS check these locations for grounded facts before making claims:

- **`/home/jcsiq98/ubermench/`** — Main codebase. Code is the source of truth for what exists today.
- **`/home/jcsiq98/ubermench-docs/`** — All project documentation:
  - `proyecto/` — `HISTORIA_DECISIONES.md`, `PIVOT_ESTRATEGICO.md`, `PIVOT_MILESTONES.md`
  - `operacion/` — `PLAN_PRUEBAS_FOUNDER.md`, `META_WHATSAPP_CHECKLIST.md`, `GUION_PRIMEROS_5_USUARIOS.md`, `PRESUPUESTO.md`
  - `research/` — `GUION_ENTREVISTAS.md`, `WORKANA_POST_RESEARCHER.md`, `tools/`
  - `sesiones/` — Deep thinking sessions
  - `arquitectura/` — ADRs
- **`/home/jcsiq98/ubermench/_archive/`** — Historical reference:
  - `handy-docs/` — LATAM market research (PDF report)
  - `ROADMAP_MARKETPLACE_V1.md` — Original marketplace roadmap (pre-pivot)
  - `STATUS_MARKETPLACE.md` — Marketplace status at time of pivot

Read these files BEFORE making claims about project strategy, history, decisions, market data, or user research. Quote directly from them.

## Constraints (ALL active simultaneously)

### 1. Say "I don't know"
If you don't have a credible source for a claim, say so. Don't guess. Don't infer. "No tengo datos sobre esto" / "I don't have data on this" is always a valid answer.

### 2. Verify with citations
Every recommendation, claim, or piece of advice must cite a specific source:
- A file in the current project (with path)
- An external source found via web search (with URL)
- A named expert, paper, or researcher
- Official documentation

If you generate a claim and cannot find a supporting source, retract it. Do not present it.

### 3. Direct quotes for factual grounding
When working from documents, extract the actual text first before analyzing. Ground your response in word-for-word quotes, not paraphrased summaries. Reference the quote when making your point.

## What this mode is NOT
- It is NOT the default. Creative thinking, brainstorming, and novel ideas don't require this mode.
- It does NOT mean "be slow." Research efficiently. Use tools in parallel.
- It does NOT mean "only use existing ideas." You can synthesize across sources to reach new conclusions, but the inputs must be grounded.

## How to exit
User says "exit research mode", "salir de modo investigación", or switches to any other task.
